Description
------------------------------------------------

This is python script that takes the following input through command line
1. destination ip address
2. interface
3. Transport Layer protocol (0:ICMP; 1:TCP; 2:UDP)
4. message


It depends on scapy package to modify header values and send packets.
The secret message is encoded in the high byte of the identifier of the IP 
packet with the sequencing information going in the fragment offset.

Execution
-----------------------------------------------
To execute the program, just run ./secret_sender


